<h2>1. Adaptation of captions in Markdown files for display in HTML with <i>jekyll-figure 0.1.0</i>.</h2>
<p>Following has been installed with <i>macOS 10.13.6</i> and is basically also usable for other operating systems; CI/CD of this GitLab repository will be adapted, too.</p>
<p><b>1.</b> 
To generate <a href="https://gitlab.gwdg.de/buddenbohm/factsheets_sshoc_services/-/tree/master/_site" target="_blank">HTML-Dateien</a> locally from <a href="https://gitlab.gwdg.de/buddenbohm/factsheets_sshoc_services/-/tree/master/_posts" target="_blank">Markdown-Dateien</a>, <a href="https://www.markdownguide.org/tools/jekyll/" target="_blank"><i>jekyll-figure 0.1.0</i></a> runs in a Docker image.</p>
<p><b>2.</b>Installed:</p>
<ul>
<li><i>Docker Desktop 2.2.2.0 (43066)</i></li>
<li><i>Docker Compose 1.25.4</i></li>
<li><i>jekyll 4.2.0</i>, <i>jekyll-figure 0.1.0</i>, <i>jekyll-sass-converter 2.1.0</i> and <i>jekyll-watch 2.2.1</i>.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3.</b> Start:</p>
<ol>
<li>Start <i>Docker Desktop</i>.</li>
<li>Type in a terminal: <code>docker-compose up</code>.</li>
</ol>
<p>Afterwards, automatically, a browser window will be opened displaying <a href="https://gitlab.gwdg.de/buddenbohm/factsheets_sshoc_services/-/tree/master/_site/index.html" target="_blank">index.html</a>.</p>
<p><b>4.</b> Displaying of captions in both Markdown source file and HTML target file <i>jekyll-figure 0.1.0</i> plugin has been installed. For this in</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td><a href="https://gitlab.gwdg.de/buddenbohm/factsheets_sshoc_services/-/blob/master/_config.yml" target="_blank">_config.yml</a></td>
<td><code>plugins:<br/>
- jekyll-figure</code></td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="https://gitlab.gwdg.de/buddenbohm/factsheets_sshoc_services/-/blob/master/docker-compose.yaml" target="_blank">docker-compose.yaml</a>:</td>
<td><code>command: ><br/>
bash -c "bundle install<br/>
&amp;&amp; jekyll serve"</code></td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="https://gitlab.gwdg.de/buddenbohm/factsheets_sshoc_services/-/blob/master/Gemfile" target="_blank">Gemfile</a></td>
<td><code>gem 'jekyll-figure'</code></td></tr>
</table>
<p>have been inserted.</p>
<h2>2. Making images clickable for display in HTML with 

